NN}/f_\rho), (f_{\omega NN}/f_\omega), (f_{\phi NN}/f_\phi)$ and
also $(f_{\omega' NN}/f_{\omega'}), (f_{\phi' NN}/f_{\phi'})$ as
free parameters of the model to be then subsequently determined
numerically in comparison of the advanced $U\&A$ model with all
existing data simultaneously.

