of the nucleon EM FFs, is achieved by the non-linear
transformations

$t = t^s_0 + \frac{4(t^{1s}_{in}-t^s_0)}{[1/V(t)-V(t)]^2};$\quad
$t = t^v_0 +\frac{4(t^{1v}_{in}-t^v_0)}{[1/W(t)-W(t)]^2};$\\

$t = t^s_0 + \frac{4(t^{2s}_{in}-t^s_0)}{[1/U(t)-U(t)]^2};$\quad
$t = t^v_0 + \frac{4(t^{2v}_{in}-t^v_0)}{[1/X(t)-X(t)]^2},$\\
respectively and a subsequent inclusion of the nonzero values of
vector-meson widths.

